      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Keen to stick with BRUISER MURPHY (3) who ran some slick late sectionals at Pakenham in a Class 1 last start, rattling home for a narrow fifth in a handy race. The debut win prior at Moe was impressive and if he can just land midfield here he'll go mighty close. THAT'SMONEYBROTHER (6) ran a good race first up at Yarra Valley over 1000m, beaten under a length. He'll strip fitter for that and should land in a good spot for Stackhouse. EMPIRE SONG (4) ran in a much stronger race first up and faded but had shown ability prior and can do much better here. LOVING MANDY (1) was off a short break last time at Ballarat and ran a fair race, expect she can strip fitter here. PRINCE PIENZA (5) comes off a narrow maiden win with minor claims.",
